column5: hi all,got out saturday 26th on the bay of quinte,deseronto and caught my personal best walleye.930am i was jigging a fin tech jig and gulp 3 minnow and landed 11 lbs walleye.
nice going  that is the place for PB walleye
Awesome PB kevin    Congrats And welcome to OFC Leechman
Welcome aboard Kevin. A great looking eye... congrats and thanks for post the pic.
Wtg!.. was that the only fish for the day?
Welcome to the board & Nice Walleye Richard
Quinte always produces hawgs, & that's another excellent example !!  Great fish indeed !!
A warm welcome aboard Kevin. Awesome fish!
Nice catch. Congrats. Can you be more specific of what  fin tech jig did you use?
Nice Pickereye! A suggestion if I may be so bold, if you are not planning on keeping that beauty, you may want to consider supporting the belly of the fish when taking pics. Again, nice Pickereye! HH

welcome to OFC Kevin. Check out an online account like photobucket or imageshack to share your pic's.  they take up no space on this server and they are a much larger pic for all to see.  just a thought as I can't tell if you are holding a fish or real bad moldy stick of french loaf...    right Roy
